messages.content:
@Development Please read #deleted-channel for context.

We need two bots:
1. Takes the Airtable applications and posts them in the twitter thread.
2. Every hour post the leaderboard of applications (sorted by retweets) and the time until the competition/race ends.

Also check out #deleted-channel if you can help market this!

Who's up for this?
I’ve got it
cc: @m1guelpf @longtran @neelr @rorhug @nathan.eth
Can you send a@head.ai Airtable access and any other existing bot tooling to build on top of?
i'm down to help. have you started yet?
Also curious if there are remaining needs and what kind of timeline we are looking at

Should we say all applications due by X date, and post all submissions at that time? (rather than having the bot post as soon as an air table receives a submission) 

Seems like first to submit will have a large advantage over others and I don't think first to submit the application should influence the decision too heavily

If you batched them all at once and tweeted them out.. still the first one would have an advantage of getting the "easy" retweets. As people read the other ones they'd get a bit worn out. It's almost better if they are spaced out as submitted.
Unless there's a low amount of submissions (most likely won't be), which in that case I agree.

yeah thats a good point, first would still get the most reads.

Maybe we keep it spaced out and be sure to include on the leader board the newly submitted applications to help give them more visability?
I think having it that way creates a bit of urgency
Also for the stack I think we should go node for just development speed and unofficial Twitter api https://github.com/ttezel/twit

messages.content: The benefit of the first getting the most reads is it incentivizes people to apply more. Creates FOMO. So from a marketing perspective I see a case for real-time posting
For #1 Airtable to twitter could be an easy zapier. #2 def use something like that I'd presume.
The Node API looks pretty sweet. I was thinking about doing all of this in Airtable and Integromat. I'm looking at the Twitter API now and testing it out with Postman
The tricky bit is dealing with threads but it looks doable so far
Im convinced to NOT batch all the applications 🙂 good points
I was hoping AT would work directly for #1 but you can't post in threads with it
@kevalin the question I have here is will this be one ongoing thread, or will we have one thread of applications per week, or something like that?
Seems like there's more marketing opportunity to having a concept of "weekly cohorts" or similar
Just checked zapier and it's the same. Code it is lol
I'm still confident we can do this with no-code tools. We just need to use the Twitter API directly
I’ll get started on a code solution because that’ll probably be more sustainable long term
One more note on the airtable part. Do we want to make sure there's a check before it's tweeted out? If there's no boolean in airtable saying it's okay to tweet out we might see a lot of spam 😅
Good point. We'd probably need someone manually reviewing which ones get tweeted. So we could setup a trigger in Airtable that they could click to approve and tweet it
Couldn't hurt
Do we have a repo yet? I can help with that, I have used Twitter API before
Putting this on pause
Will explain in 30 min
Good point. This project has been paused.
We're going to build this referral system on a website
Not twitter
any details?
Yeah we're going to build this into the website
This is all phase #2 stuff
After our launch in a few hours

@Development this is an excerpt from what I sent to the core.

This marketing campaign—dubbed the “nuke”—has been set aside. This nuke version is too spammy. It’ll also be botted on Twitter. Not a good look. Will tarnish our reputation.

We know it’d generate tons of hype. Many people will apply & join the community. Hyperscale isn’t ready. We need a strong product that we’ll build these viral loops into.

We’re going to build these launch ideas into our product—a one-click DAO formation form & an investment marketplace. BTW our product is very open-ended. Need to trial investments and see what the DAOs & the community needs. These are just ideas in a direction: ecosystem support.

Today we’re doing a small launch. The main objective is to get applications. We also want to grow the community. This is a small win that’ll rally everyone around phase #2 of Hyperscale.
We're going to build a share for % of investment & weekly DAO competitions (think Mirror write race) into the website.
This is part of phase #2 which will launch in 1-2 weeks.
Yeah this is one of the reasons I mentioned at least having a check in Airtable before it gets sent out. But even that doesn't stop someone from bot retweeting their own project 😄
This all makes sense. Love the vision
Hey David! I know how to build Twitter bots, do you want to add me to the repo so I can help?
Project is on pause right now
Yeah down to collaborate once we decide to prioritize this

Could someone here make a post wrt this channel summarising:

1). What has been completed so far
2). What are the next 3-5 big priorities 

We can then pin this to help new people contribute effectively, every day it gets harder to scroll back and read through to catch up. So this would really help.
Yes would be very helpful! Also please do this for all building category channels

For the twitter bot, I’ve specced it lightly, setup the database, got the Twitter API connected, and started working on getting it to post properly in a thread. Paused since @kevalin said to pause though
